Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Platform Engineer, Data & Analytics Platforms* position with *The Hershey Company*. I bring over three years of professional experience in platform engineering, observability, infrastructure-as-code, and MLOps, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across multiple engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade platform operations systems that directly reflect the technical depth and operational focus this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a platform operations layer enabling self-service execution of 1,000+ API endpoints through automated workflows and infrastructure-as-code, reducing time-to-value for product teams while improving reliability through governance guardrails—directly mirroring Hershey's need to turn one-off solutions into reusable templates and automated workflows. To keep these systems production-ready, I built observability infrastructure using Langfuse and LangSmith for monitoring, logging, alerting, and tracing, enabling proactive detection, root-cause analysis, and incident management to reduce MTTR—the same operational discipline Hershey requires for maintaining platform health and meeting service levels. I also optimized platform performance and cost transparency through concurrency tuning, reducing latency by 60% and API costs by 50% through FinOps-aligned optimization, demonstrating the cost monitoring and optimization capabilities central to this role. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO, implementing infrastructure-as-code for environment provisioning and standardization—giving me direct experience with multi-cloud platform operations and environment consistency. I also developed automation workflows using AWS Step Functions and Lambda with infrastructure-as-code (CloudFormation) and CI/CD, improving reliability via operational runbooks—the same CI/CD and infrastructure-as-code practices Hershey emphasizes for platform delivery. Together, these roles have prepared me to own and operate core data platform components, implement observability and operational standards, and enable Data Product teams through self-service tooling and automation.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in MLOps, platform operations, and technical enablement—skills that translate directly into the MLOps capabilities and collaborative culture this role values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I operated ML platform infrastructure on an HPC cluster using CUDA and PyTorch for model training, fine-tuning, and deployment of StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion models. I implemented MLOps patterns using vLLM for inference and Hugging Face for secure serving, establishing operational standards for model lifecycle management—directly aligning with Hershey's need to enable MLOps capabilities in partnership with Data Science and engineering teams. Beyond building the systems myself, I enabled platform adoption through self-service tooling and conducted workshops on GPU programming and AI Agents for 50+ students, improving onboarding and knowledge-sharing—directly mirroring the platform enablement, training, and clear intake processes central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who operates platforms with rigor, enables teams through self-service tooling and documentation, and communicates technical solutions effectively across domains.

I have always been passionate about *togetherness, integrity, making a difference, and excellence*—values that guide how I build platforms and enable teams—and envision myself contributing my talent to furthering Hershey's mission of *creating undeniably pleasurable experiences for all* through trusted, governed data platforms at scale. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

